# Socrate — Superadmin Portal · Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend-for-Frontend (BFF) model
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The SPA is a PURE COOKIE CLIENT. It holds NO tokens and NO OAuth client
# config: the BFF (see bff/) is the confidential OAuth client. It runs the
# Authorization Code + PKCE flow server-side, keeps the tokens in a server-side
# session, and the browser only ever holds an opaque HttpOnly session cookie.
#
# In production, Caddy serves the SPA and reverse-proxies `/bff/*` and
# `/api/admin/*` to the BFF (same origin) — so the SPA talks to ITS OWN origin
# and these vars are normally left UNSET (same-origin defaults). See deploy/.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTIONAL
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Admin API origin. Leave UNSET for the same-origin BFF deployment (the SPA
# calls relative `/api/admin/*` and the BFF injects the bearer). Set to an
# absolute HTTPS origin only for split-origin setups. MUST be https:// in prod.
#   • same-origin (BFF):  (leave unset)
# VITE_ADMIN_API_URL=

# Public OIDC issuer origin — used ONLY for the public, pre-auth flows the BFF
# does not proxy (forgot/reset password). Leave UNSET for same-origin / dev
# proxy. MUST be https:// in production when set.
#   • split-port dev:  http://localhost:8080
#   • production:      https://socrate.your-domain.com
# VITE_OIDC_ISSUER=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Local dev (npm run dev)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Vite dev server proxies `/bff/*` and `/api/admin/*` to a locally-running
# BFF on :8091 (run the BFF from bff/ with its own .env), and the public issuer
# flows (`/api/auth/*`, `/api/profile`, `/oauth/*`) to the backend on :8080.
# With that topology in place, both vars above stay unset in dev too.
